---
<Base title="Areas We Cover | SEO Across Swansea & South Wales | SEO Swansea" description="SEO services covering every Swansea neighbourhood from Mumbles and Sketty to Morriston and SA1 Waterfront, plus wider South Wales including Neath and Llanelli." schema={schema}>

  <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">Home</a>
    <span class="mx-1">/</span>
    <span class="text-gray-700">Areas</span>
  </nav>

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-brand mb-4">Areas We Cover — SEO Across Swansea and South Wales</h1>

  <div class="bg-rose-50 border-l-4 border-accent p-4 rounded-r-lg my-6">
    <p class="text-text/80 font-medium">We work with businesses from Mumbles seafront to Morriston Hospital, SA1 Waterfront to Sketty Cross, and right across South Wales — Neath, Port Talbot, Llanelli, Carmarthen, and Bridgend. Knowing these neighbourhoods inside out means sharper keyword targeting and quicker results for you.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We cover the full geographic spread of Swansea and the surrounding South Wales region. Every area has its own commercial character, search habits, and competitive picture. A restaurant in Mumbles faces completely different SEO challenges to a tech startup at SA1 Waterfront or a manufacturing firm near Swansea Enterprise Park. We shape every campaign around the specific area your business serves, going after the keywords and map pack spots that actually bring in local revenue.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Below is a detailed look at the areas we work in, the kinds of businesses we help in each spot, and how local SEO plays out in each neighbourhood. If your area isn't on the list, <a href="/contact/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">drop us a message</a> — chances are we cover it.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Mumbles</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Mumbles is Swansea's crown jewel on the coast and one of the most searched-for spots in South Wales. It draws a mix of tourism searches and local commercial queries. Mumbles Pier, the Lighthouse, and the seafront promenade bring year-round visitor interest, while the village itself is packed with independent restaurants, boutique shops, ice cream spots, and accommodation.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">SEO for Mumbles businesses has to capture both the tourist crowd and the locals. We go after seasonal keywords like "Mumbles restaurants" and "things to do in Mumbles" that spike in summer, while keeping visibility ticking over for year-round searches like "Mumbles dentist" or "Mumbles estate agents." Google Business Profile work is especially powerful here because the map pack dominates mobile searches from visitors strolling the seafront.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Link building in Mumbles is a joy. Local tourism boards, Visit Swansea Bay, food blogs, and travel publications love featuring Mumbles content, which creates natural backlink opportunities for businesses with solid websites.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Sketty</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Sketty is one of Swansea's leafiest and most well-off suburbs, centred around Sketty Cross. It's got a busy local high street with independent shops, dental practices, estate agents, takeaways, and professional services. Being close to Singleton Hospital and Swansea University, it also picks up healthcare and student-related searches.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Local SEO in Sketty targets the residential population hunting for nearby services. Keywords like "dentist Sketty," "takeaway Sketty," and "estate agent Sketty" have consistent monthly search volume with competition you can actually crack. We build location pages, tidy up Google Business Profiles, and make sure your business appears in the map pack when Sketty residents go looking for local help.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Morriston</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Morriston is a major commercial and healthcare hub in north Swansea. Morriston Hospital is the biggest in the Swansea Bay University Health Board area, which drives a huge amount of healthcare-related search volume. The DVLA headquarters and Phoenix Trading Estate bring plenty of B2B and public sector search traffic too.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">SEO for Morriston businesses often means targeting service-area keywords rather than foot-traffic queries. Trade businesses, suppliers, and B2B companies near the trading estates need to show up for searches that include "Swansea" or "SA6" rather than just "Morriston." We build campaigns that grab both the hyperlocal Morriston queries and the broader Swansea searches that businesses here can serve.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Healthcare providers near Morriston Hospital can really benefit from proximity-based SEO. Patients looking for physiotherapy, dental care, or specialist clinics often search "near Morriston Hospital," creating a valuable keyword cluster that most competitors don't even think about.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Uplands</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Uplands is Swansea's bohemian quarter — known for its independent cafes, vintage shops, and buzzing food scene along Uplands Crescent. It's got a strong community feel and attracts searches from locals and visitors alike who want something different from the city centre chains.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">SEO for Uplands businesses leans heavily on Google Business Profile work and locally flavoured content. The area's independent character means customers actively search for "independent cafe Uplands" or "vintage shop Swansea Uplands" instead of generic brand terms. We help Uplands businesses own these niche searches through targeted listings, review management, and local blog content that builds genuine authority.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">SA1 Waterfront</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">SA1 Waterfront is Swansea's regenerated docklands and the city's main tech and startup district. The Technium building, coworking spaces, and digital agencies clustered here make SA1 the beating heart of Swansea's knowledge economy. Waterfront restaurants and the new arena development add leisure and entertainment search volume on top.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">SEO for SA1 businesses usually targets a wider audience than other Swansea neighbourhoods. Tech companies and agencies based here serve clients across Wales and the UK, so campaigns blend local Swansea visibility with broader regional and national keyword targeting. We build topical authority around your core services while keeping the local signals strong enough to hold your Swansea-specific visibility.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">The SA1 postcode carries a bit of prestige in Swansea search. Businesses that weave their SA1 location into their SEO strategy benefit from the area's modern, professional reputation. We work SA1 and Waterfront references into title tags, meta descriptions, and Google Business Profile copy to make the most of that positioning.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Gorseinon and Gowerton</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Gorseinon and Gowerton sit on the western edge of the Swansea urban area, acting as gateway towns to Gower Peninsula and Llanelli. They've got growing populations, active high streets, and a healthy mix of retail, trade, and service businesses that all stand to gain from local SEO.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">SEO competition in Gorseinon and Gowerton is noticeably lighter than in central Swansea. A well-set-up Google Business Profile and a couple of targeted landing pages can grab top positions for local service keywords within weeks. We help businesses here punch well above their weight by picking up searches that bigger Swansea competitors simply overlook.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Wider South Wales</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Neath and Port Talbot</h3>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Neath and Port Talbot sit just east of Swansea as the neighbouring county borough. Neath town centre has a solid independent retail scene, while Port Talbot revolves around the Tata Steel works and its industrial supply chain. SEO for businesses here targets both local residents and the industrial workforce. We build campaigns that capture "Neath" and "Port Talbot" searches alongside broader "Swansea area" terms.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Llanelli</h3>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Llanelli is the biggest town in Carmarthenshire, just 20 minutes west of Swansea. The Millennium Coastal Path, Parc y Scarlets, and the town's retail parks keep local search volume ticking along nicely. Plenty of Llanelli businesses compete for the same customers as Swansea businesses, especially in trades, healthcare, and professional services. We help Llanelli businesses build local SEO that holds its own against Swansea-based competitors.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Carmarthen and Bridgend</h3>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Carmarthen and Bridgend mark the western and eastern edges of our regular coverage area. Both are county towns with strong local economies, university presences, and growing digital sectors. We run SEO campaigns for businesses in these towns that want to capture local traffic and compete regionally across South Wales. For businesses that serve the whole M4 corridor from Carmarthen to Bridgend, we build regional campaigns that target multiple towns at once.</p>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Curious how your business ranks in your specific area? Our free audit shows you exactly where your local visibility stands and what you're missing out on.</p>
    <a href="/free-seo-audit-swansea/" class="bg-accent text-brand px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-accent/80 font-semibold inline-block">Grab Your Free Local SEO Audit</a>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2 px-4">Can you zero in on specific Swansea postcodes?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed px-4 pb-4">Yes. We build location-focused landing pages and set up your Google Business Profile service areas to target individual postcodes from SA1 through SA8. This works brilliantly for trade businesses, delivery services, and home service providers who need to rank in specific patches rather than the whole city.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2 px-4">Are you only for businesses in Swansea city centre?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed px-4 pb-4">Not at all. We work with businesses right across the Swansea county area — Mumbles, Sketty, Morriston, Uplands, Gorseinon, Gowerton, and everywhere in between. We also cover Neath, Port Talbot, Llanelli, Carmarthen, and Bridgend. If your business serves customers in any of these areas, we can put together a campaign that targets your specific patch.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2 px-4">Is it worth investing in SEO for a smaller town like Gorseinon or Gowerton?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed px-4 pb-4">Absolutely. Smaller towns tend to have much less SEO competition, which means faster results and lower costs. A well-optimised Google Business Profile and a handful of locally targeted pages can dominate search results in places like Gorseinon, Gowerton, or Pontarddulais within weeks rather than months.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2 px-4">Do you reach as far as Neath, Port Talbot, and Llanelli?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed px-4 pb-4">We cover them all. Our reach stretches across the wider South Wales region. We run campaigns for businesses in Neath, Port Talbot, Llanelli, Carmarthen, and Bridgend. Many of these areas have decent search volume with surprisingly low competition compared to Cardiff or Bristol, making them cracking opportunities for local SEO.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2 px-4">What's your approach for tourism businesses on the Gower?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed px-4 pb-4">Tourism SEO needs a seasonal game plan. We get content and optimisation firing before peak summer months, keep accommodation and activity keywords working year-round, and build links from travel publications and local tourism boards. Gower businesses benefit from strong search volume around Rhossili Bay, Three Cliffs Bay, and the Wales Coast Path. We also make sure your Google Maps visibility is spot on, which is crucial for visitors finding their way around the coast.</p>
    </details>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-brand/5 border border-brand/20 rounded-lg p-6 my-8 text-center">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mb-3">Find Out How You Rank Locally</h2>
    <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Whether you're in Mumbles, Morriston, or anywhere across South Wales, we'll show you exactly where your local SEO stands and what it takes to move up.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
      <a href="/contact/" class="bg-accent text-brand px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-accent/80 font-semibold inline-block">Let's Chat</a>
      <a href="/services/" class="border border-accent text-accent px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-accent hover:text-brand inline-block font-semibold">View Services</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</Base>
